Class
Description
AbstractPuzzle
Abstract base class for all puzzles like Sudoku, Killer and Str8ts that have a square grid with the constraints that each number has to be in the range from 1 to the number of rows/columns in the grid (see AbstractPuzzle.getGridSize()) and no duplicate values are allowed in a row/column.
AbstractPuzzle.Cell
A cell in the grid of a Puzzle in the form of an ordered nominal Pair (row, column).
AbstractPuzzle.SetCellResult
Result of setCell().
AbstractPuzzle.SolveResult
Result of AbstractPuzzle.solve().
AbstractSudoku
Abstract base class for all Sudoku-like puzzles like Sudoku and Killer with the additional constraint of sub-grids with unique values.

Str8ts
Concrete final implementation of AbstractPuzzle with the additional constraints of colored cells (white cells are just like every other cell in an AbstractPuzzle, black cells can be empty) and straights (each compartment of white cells must contain a set of consecutive numbers in any order).
Str8ts.Color
